Step-by-Step Installation Workflow (Texas Residential)¹

Use this one-page flow as a field checklist. Adapt fastener counts to the wind-zone table in [fasteners_standard] or [fasteners_high_wind].

flowchart TD
    A[Site Prep & Safety]\n• PPE / harness\n• Material staging --> B[Deck Inspection]\n• Replace rot\n• Flush nails
    B --> C[Surface Prep]\n• Sweep debris\n• Verify <16% MC
    C --> D[Underlayment]\nZone 1: synthetic\nZone 3: full S-A
    D --> E{Batten or Direct?}
    E -- Direct --> F[Snap chalk lines]\n3-12 slope min
    E -- Battens --> F2[Install 2×2 battens]\n24" o.c.; fasten into rafters
    F & F2 --> G[Starter & Eave Metal]\nSeal butyl strip
    G --> H[Lay Field Panels]\nInterlock L→R; 4-7 screws / panel
    H --> I[Trim & Flashing]\nValleys, sidewall, chimney
    I --> J[Ridge Vent & Caps]\nVent roll + foam closures
    J --> K[Final QC]\n25-in-lb torque\nPhoto docs for WPI-8

Key Best-Practice Reminders
	•	Fasteners: Stainless or HDG #10 in field; #12 at edges in Zone 3.
	•	Thermal allowance: Drive screws centered in slots; do not over-torque.
	•	Walk zones: Step only in lower pan over battens/deck to avoid dents.
	•	Documentation: For coastal counties, photograph fastener pattern before ridge caps—required for WPI-8.

Typical Crew Sequence & Time (30-square roof)

Phase	Crew size	Avg hrs
Tear-off & Deck Repair	4	4–6
Dry-in / Underlayment	3	2
Batten / Chalk Layout	3	1.5
Panel + Trim Install	5	8–10
QC & Cleanup	2	1

Total 1.5–2 days in good weather; add 20 % for complex hips or >12:12 pitch.

